The paper proposes a new model for generating textual explanations for images, which involves grounding constituent phrases in the image to ensure relevance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of a phrase-critic model and a ranking loss function suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on image relevance and scoring suggests that it may also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
